org.jdesktop.core.animation.timing.interpolators

Class AccelerationInterpolator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jdesktop.core.animation.timing.interpolators.AccelerationInterpolator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Interpolator

    @Immutable
public class AccelerationInterpolator
extends java.lang.Object
implements Interpolator
    This class interpolates fractional values to animate movement with acceleration at the beginning and deceleration at the end.

    Instances of this class contain no mutable state and can be safely shared. This class is thread-safe.

    Author:
    Chet Haase, Tim Halloran

      • interpolate

        @RegionEffects(value="reads Instance")
public double interpolate(double fraction)
        Description copied from interface: Interpolator
        This function takes an input value between 0 and 1 and returns another value, also between 0 and 1. The purpose of the function is to define how time (represented as a (0-1) fraction of the duration of an animation) is altered to derive different value calculations during an animation.
        Specified by:
        interpolate in interface Interpolator
        Parameters:
        fraction - a value between 0 and 1, inclusive, representing the elapsed fraction of a time interval.
        Returns:
        a value between 0 and 1, inclusive. Values outside of this boundary may be clamped to the interval [0,1] and cause undefined results.
